				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Leveling, Easy or Hard?<a name="75475"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 15 05 2:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Here is what my friend does with the druid...
<br />

<br />
Get high enough level for your first AoE DD song (2 - Chords of Dissonance) level 2 woot! hehe, anyways...
<br />

<br />
What my friend does is buff the druid (hp, regen, but no DS) and will pull... just a MASS amount of mobs (usually with AoE snare on druid) and just keep pulling, and pulling and pulling (watching him do this to my friend with about 40 mobs) then, once the druid has enough, stop. once the mobs are standing there (have to be still for the AoE DoT to hit) cast you aoe song. after your aoe hits the mobs just once, then cast the DS's on the druid. Usually my friend would cast the self one, normal  one, then the Spirit of the Wood aa. And wammmo!! exp like you woulndt beleive.
<br />

<br />
In my opinion, when I PL any of my character, I always use single killing , with DS, regen, hp buffs from the druid. That way my skills still go up, and don't completely suck at higher levels. 
<br />

<br />
I have a cleric friend that I pled, and he would just kill 1 mob at a time, that cons red. So he is now level 55 cleric (in about 3 weeks) and he tanks better then my 60 bard, or better then even most tanks he encounters. I beleive its because his defense skill is maxed out from being PLed like that, always getting hit by a mob. Most clerics normal leveling, don't reallly get their defense skill up. 
<br />

<br />
and still... he makes me mad  when I talk about how hard a mob hits and he just steps in and tanks it and takes half the damage!!! i'm like, wtf!!! ^.^ hehe.</span></td>
